<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Oct 28 16:09:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all,<br><br>
I am a better father because I went to Vietnam.  I've seen the results of too much &quot;drama&quot; in the world when people draw &quot;lines in the sand.&quot;  Therefore comedy is king in my house and not the conflicts of drama.<br><br>
I have learned to wear different coats because I went to Vietnam.  I have learned to reconcile the words of Chief Joseph, I WILL FIGHT NO MORE FOREVER to knowing that fighting is necessary for history to progress.  Power is seldom (if ever) shared rationally with people with different viewpoints. <br><br>
I have learned not to take the Republicans or Democrats too seriously.  They are each in business for themselves and will do whatever it takes to keep their power bases strong.<br><br>
I've have learned tolerance because I was a soldier in Vietnam.  We don't all have to think alike.  Our different backgrounds and experiences add to life.<br><br>
I have learned and relearned a meaning behind the maxin &quot;THERE BUT FOR THE GRACE OF GOD GO I.&quot;<br><br>
I have &quot;learned&quot; not to care whether a God exists or not.  It is up to us to create our own worlds.<br><br>
I have learned that I will never be able to live up to my ideals, but that they are still worth pursuing -- it's really the only game in town.<br><br>
I have leaned not to take life too seriously and at the same time knowing full well that life  is serious business and should be treated as such.<br><br>
I have learned that there are two things that you can't tell someone.  One is that they didn't do their job and two is that they don't have a sense of humor.<br><br>
I learned that it was better for me to go to Vietnam than not, but I know that for others the opposite is true.<br><br>
I tell my daughter that America is more than a country -- it is an idea that people can live freely together -- with tolerance.  I know that I keep repeating the word tolerance over and over again.  Pain taught me that.<br><br>
I've learned that there are many &quot;really smart&quot; people on this chat line and some may wonder why I put really smart in quotation marks.  My idea of humor.<br><br>
I learned that I like this chat line and will remain.<br><br>
I hopefully learned not to run on, so as not to bore too many people<br><br>
Paul<br><br>
PS -- This message being sent without proofreading.  A little more humor from the Pagemaker<br><br>
